geo:siteIdentification.geo:notes: Basaltic Lava. The lava is glacialy scoured. The Survey Marker Bolt is anchored into the concrete of the balustrade wall on the top of the elevator tower in the building for the Engineering Research Institute in the University Reykjavik. The antenna is 13.5 m above the ground, 1.5 m above the roof of the building, 0.5 m above the roof of the elevator tower and 0.2 m above the balustrade wall. The building foundation is 21 m to the rock. In addition an ASHTECH Z-18 GPS+GLONASS receiver was operating from 1998-09-11 until 2004-10-05 and a JPS LEGACY GPS+GLONASS receiver was operating from 2004-10-05 until 2007-09-19, four character ID REYZ, Domes No. 10202M003.
